# Code Review & Branching

**Before opening or reviewing any PR:** read `docs/09-development/CODE-REVIEW-GUIDE.md` + `docs/09-development/BRANCHING-STRATEGY.md`

## Branch Naming

```
{type}/{scope}-{short-description}
feature/installments-waive-api
fix/installment-overdue-timezone
hotfix/payment-confirm-race
```

Types: `feature` · `fix` · `chore` · `docs` · `refactor` · `test` · `hotfix`

## Commit Format (Conventional Commits)

```
{type}({scope}): {description}
feat(installments): add waive use case with audit
fix(rbac): deny override not overriding role grant
```

## PR Author — Automatic Blocks (must fix before request review)

```
❌ prisma.*.delete() on any business entity
❌ number/float for financial amounts — bigint Rial only
❌ tenantId from request body — JWT only
❌ Business logic in Controller / Bot Handler / React component
❌ Missing permission guard on staff endpoint
❌ console.log in production code paths
❌ Secrets or credentials committed
❌ Missing regression test for financial bug fix
❌ ADR missing for new architecture decision
```

## PR Size Limits

| Type | Max Lines |
|------|-----------|
| Feature | 500 |
| Bug fix | 200 |
| Refactor | 300 |
| Migration | 150 |

**One concern per PR** — no drive-by refactoring.

## Hotfix

```
1. Branch from main — git checkout -b hotfix/xxx
2. Write regression test FIRST (financial bugs)
3. Fix + commit
4. PR → 1 approval (expedited)
5. Post-review within 24h
```

## Merge Strategy

- **Squash and merge** — one clean commit per PR on `main`
- **Rebase** onto `main` before opening PR — not merge
- Delete branch after merge

